### PMP Progress Tracker API Requests - EXAMPLE FILE
### Copy this to pmp-tracker.http and add real access codes
### Base URL: https://pmp-progress-tracker.vercel.app

### Get all students
GET https://pmp-progress-tracker.vercel.app/api/students
Accept: application/json

### Add a new student
POST https://pmp-progress-tracker.vercel.app/api/students
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test Student",
  "email": "test@example.com"
}

### Add student (name only)
POST https://pmp-progress-tracker.vercel.app/api/students
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Another Student"
}

### Get all course modules
GET https://pmp-progress-tracker.vercel.app/api/modules
Accept: application/json

### Get all progress records
GET https://pmp-progress-tracker.vercel.app/api/progress
Accept: application/json

### Get progress for specific student (change ID as needed)
GET https://pmp-progress-tracker.vercel.app/api/progress?studentId=1
Accept: application/json

### Update student progress
POST https://pmp-progress-tracker.vercel.app/api/progress
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "studentId": 1,
  "moduleId": 1,
  "percentage": 75
}

### Update another progress example
POST https://pmp-progress-tracker.vercel.app/api/progress
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "studentId": 2,
  "moduleId": 3,
  "percentage": 100
}

### Admin login
POST https://pmp-progress-tracker.vercel.app/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "type": "admin",
  "password": "YOUR_ADMIN_PASSWORD"
}

### Student login - Example
# Replace YOUR_ACCESS_CODE with actual access code
POST https://pmp-progress-tracker.vercel.app/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "type": "student",
  "accessCode": "YOUR_ACCESS_CODE"
}

